summary: This is an email exchange between FBI agents following the arrest of Ghislaine Maxwell on July 2, 2020. It contains expressions of gratitude and professional praise between the New York FBI team and the Bedford, New Hampshire FBI team for their collaboration and execution of the arrest operation.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: The subject of the email is 'Maxwell arrest', indicating she was the target of the FBI operation being discussed.

connections.description: SA was part of the FBI team that assisted in the arrest operation targeting Ghislaine Maxwell.

events.title: Arrest of Ghislaine Maxwell
events.description: The FBI executed an operation resulting in the arrest of Ghislaine Maxwell. The email praises the successful execution of 'today's entry'.

keyFacts: The email confirms the FBI arrest of Ghislaine Maxwell occurred on or before July 2, 2020.
The operation involved collaboration between the FBI New York office and the FBI Bedford, New Hampshire Resident Agency.
The arrest operation is described as having gone extremely well, with specific praise for an agent referred to as 'SA'.
The correspondence highlights internal FBI satisfaction and professionalism regarding a major case.
